[rung13] wrote /content/cancer-recog-apoptosis/runs/rung13_apoptosis/rung13_apoptosis.json

  kinetic safe q_n ceiling: 0.17 (~8.6x bar 0.02) | RUNG-12P/B 2D 0.3

  DECISIVE: POSITIVE (recognition->death link closes in silico): EARM-calibrated coupled cells give (1) an all-or-none excitable threshold S*=0.002 with a variable delay (Td 3.88->0.69h across dose) and a fast snap (Ts=0.55h < Td); (2) an IRREVERSIBLE commitment -- the threshold crossing latches death (a brief supra pulse still commits; sustained sub-threshold never does) and the dead state persists at zero input -- so Shriya 6.3 'cannot back out' is a dynamical property, not an assumption; (3) a BOUNDED death wave clearing the tumour (>=80% over q_n in [0.0,0.95]) while keeping normal kill <=1% up to q_n~0.17 (~8.6x the per-cell bar 0.02); (4) this CONFIRMS RUNG-12P/B's binary abstraction (2D ceiling 0.3) under real kinetics -- the recognition relaxation is EARNED. Bonus: the wave clears even heavily-primed tumour (resistance-resistance). Efficacy still needs tumour fidelity q_t above the propagation threshold; mapping c/g to molecular efficiencies is the wet-lab residual.
